OL,12,FThroughout the trial, questions were
OL,13,Fraised about whether climbers explore
OL,14,Fmountains at their own risk and the
OL,15,Flegal liability they have when
OL,16,Fclimbing high mountains.
OL,18,FDuring the trial, the prosecution
OL,19,Fargued that the defendant effectively
OL,20,Facted as a mountain guide due to his
OL,21,Fgreater level of experience.
